"{\"uid\": \"cnn.com-2024-07-25-opinions-olympics-swimming-pools-drowning-children-cullen-jones\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Follow: Editor's Note:Cullen Jones is a two-time Olympian and a four-time Olympic medalist.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23, \"end\": 35, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cullen_Jones\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cullen Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cullen_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cullen_Jones\"}, {\"begin\": 50, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999504325, \"rank\": 4.951657724620504e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 6}, {\"ngram\": \"Editor's Note\", \"from\": 8, \"to\": 21}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-time Olympic medalist\", \"from\": 62, \"to\": 90}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He partners with the USA Swimming Foundation and Make a Splash Foundation to provide drowning prevention education and motivational speaking.\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 114, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Splash Foundation\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 166}, {\"ngram\": \"drowning prevention education\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 207}, {\"ngram\": \"motivational speaking\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow him on X and Instagram at @CullenJones.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 249, \"to\": 250}, {\"ngram\": \"Instagram\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 264}, {\"ngram\": \"@CullenJones\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opinions expressed in this essay are his own.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 331, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opinions\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"this essay\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 318}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Readmore opinionat CNN.\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3756500553826487e-14, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After nearly drowning at the age of five, I could never have dreamt that one day I would swim competitively, let alone twice at the Olympics - or that I would become thefirst Black swimmer to hold a world record.\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 389}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 497}, {\"ngram\": \"thefirst Black swimmer\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"a world record\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident happened, as these occurrences often do, in a setting where kids are supposed to have fun, on a water ride at an amusement park just outside of Philadelphia.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8055223032490724e-16, \"text\": \"Philadelphia\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The incident\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 583}, {\"ngram\": \"these occurrences\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"a setting\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"kids\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"fun\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"a water ride\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"an amusement park\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 711}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My parents were nearby and a lifeguard was on duty, but somehow the responsible adults lost sight of me long enough for me to end up underwater.\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My parents\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 753}, {\"ngram\": \"a lifeguard\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"duty\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 793}, {\"ngram\": \"the responsible adults\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"sight\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I had to be resuscitated by a lifeguard and felt traumatized by the ordeal, but luckily did not suffer any long-term physical effects from it.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lifeguard\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 927}, {\"ngram\": \"the ordeal\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"any long-term physical effects\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And my parents wasted no time in signing me up for swimming lessons.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my parents\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1045}, {\"ngram\": \"no time\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming lessons\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Grit and perseverance guided me to where I am today.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Grit\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"perseverance\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, my journey - like that of many swimmers competing at this summer's Olympics in Paris - was only made possible by my ability to access a public pool.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999915712579, \"rank\": 8.428518297568093e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my journey\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"many swimmers\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"this summer's Olympics\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1241}, {\"ngram\": \"my ability\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"a public pool\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that access did not come easy: I took two buses and traveled 30 minutes from my elementary school to the Rutgers Aquatic Center in Newark, New Jersey.\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutgers_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999999276952, \"rank\": 5.90485483843716e-11, \"text\": \"Rutgers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutgers_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutgers_University\"}, {\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.44435160373197e-18, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that access\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"two buses\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1366}, {\"ngram\": \"my elementary school\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"Newark\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It became my sanctuary from the gang violence and poverty-stricken area I grew up in.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my sanctuary\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"the gang violence\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1515}, {\"ngram\": \"poverty-stricken area\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether to prevent a near-drowning like mine or to cool off during increasingly hot summer months, accessible public pools are vital to the health of entire communities.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mine\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"increasingly hot summer months\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"accessible public pools\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"the health\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"entire communities\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1725}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, too many communities today lack an affordable community pool of their own.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"too many communities\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"an affordable community pool\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Accessible public pools are vital to the health of entire communities.\\\"\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Accessible public pools\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"the health\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1866}, {\"ngram\": \"entire communities\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Majority-Black communities continue to experience thelegacy of structural racismfrom when pools were among the most segregated public places in our country.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Majority-Black communities\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1920}, {\"ngram\": \"thelegacy\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"structural racismfrom\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"pools\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"the most segregated public places\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2034}, {\"ngram\": \"our country\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the stigmas have emerged from that history and have become so deeply embedded in our culture that we even repeat them to each other: \\\"You know Black people do not swim!\\\"\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2228, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the stigmas\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"that history\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"our culture\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"Black people\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"is a phrase that many people in the community have internalized and tell each other - and ourselves - masking the systemic injustices around water access and safety that explain why so few of us become proficient swimmers.\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a phrase\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2240}, {\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 2246, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"the community\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"the systemic injustices\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2362}, {\"ngram\": \"water access\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"safety\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2393}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"proficient swimmers\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Have you ever wondered why backyard pools became so popular?\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"backyard pools\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Heather McGhee writes inher book, \\\"The Sum of Us: What Racism Costs Everyone and How We Can Prosper Together\\\":\\\"Millions of White Americans who once swam in public for free began to pay rather than swim for free with Black people.\\\"\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_McGhee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heather McGhee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_McGhee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_McGhee\"}, {\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.685511217689424e-36, \"text\": \"White Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Americans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"inher book\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2550}, {\"ngram\": \"The Sum\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2560}, {\"ngram\": \"Us\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2566}, {\"ngram\": \"Racism\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2594}, {\"ngram\": \"Together\\\":\\\"Millions\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2637}, {\"ngram\": \"public\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"Black people\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, there are more than10 million private swimming poolsin the United States, according toan industry trade group, compared with just over 300,000 public ones.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2816, \"end\": 2829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999418078788792, \"rank\": 0.0005822600406247206, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than10 million private swimming poolsin\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"toan industry trade group\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2866}, {\"ngram\": \"just over 300,000 public ones\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Public pools\\\" includes those associated with schools, hotels and other exclusive community spaces, so the number of pools that are truly accessible to the public is even smaller.\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Public pools\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2926}, {\"ngram\": \"schools\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2966}, {\"ngram\": \"hotels\", \"from\": 2968, \"to\": 2974}, {\"ngram\": \"other exclusive community spaces\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3026}, {\"ngram\": \"pools\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3035}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 3065, \"to\": 3075}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related articleOpinion: The simple reason why so many adults can not swim In the 1960s, many public pools were filled with concrete or destroyed to avoid allowing Black Americans to swim in them.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9985221235332318, \"rank\": 0.0014800638181301656, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Related articleOpinion\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3116}, {\"ngram\": \"so many adults\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3154}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1960s\", \"from\": 3171, \"to\": 3180}, {\"ngram\": \"many public pools\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3199}, {\"ngram\": \"concrete\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3225}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, park managersopted to shut down the Historic Audubon Park Natatoriumin New Orleans, the largest public pool in the South, rather than see it integrated.\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 3294, \"to\": 3298}, {\"ngram\": \"park\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3304}, {\"ngram\": \"the Historic Audubon Park Natatoriumin New Orleans\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest public pool\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3407}, {\"ngram\": \"the South\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is just one of many examples of how racism and discrimination led to the destruction and disinvestment of public pools, the consequences of which are still evident today.\", \"from\": 3453, \"to\": 3628, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many examples\", \"from\": 3473, \"to\": 3486}, {\"ngram\": \"racism\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3500}, {\"ngram\": \"discrimination\", \"from\": 3505, \"to\": 3519}, {\"ngram\": \"the destruction\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3542}, {\"ngram\": \"disinvestment\", \"from\": 3547, \"to\": 3560}, {\"ngram\": \"public pools\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3576}, {\"ngram\": \"the consequences\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)reported in Maythat more than one-third (36.8%) of Black adults reported that they do not know how to swim, compared with 15% of all adults.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3822, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Centers\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3641}, {\"ngram\": \"Disease Control\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3661}, {\"ngram\": \"Prevention\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3676}, {\"ngram\": \"Maythat\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3701}, {\"ngram\": \"more than one-third (36.8%\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3728}, {\"ngram\": \"Black adults\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3745}, {\"ngram\": \"15%\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3807}, {\"ngram\": \"all adults\", \"from\": 3811, \"to\": 3821}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Black children ages 10-14 years drown in swimming pools at a rate that is almost8 times higherthan White children.\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Black children\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3837}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming pools\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3878}, {\"ngram\": \"a rate\", \"from\": 3882, \"to\": 3888}, {\"ngram\": \"almost8 times\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3910}, {\"ngram\": \"higherthan White children\", \"from\": 3911, \"to\": 3936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Income, too, plays a huge role in determining one's ability to swim: A2017 studyfrom the USA Swimming Foundation found that 79% of children in families with incomes under $50,000 have no or low swimming experience.\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 4152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4027, \"end\": 4039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Income\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3944}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge role\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3968}, {\"ngram\": \"one's ability\", \"from\": 3984, \"to\": 3997}, {\"ngram\": \"A2017\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4012}, {\"ngram\": \"79%\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4065}, {\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4077}, {\"ngram\": \"families\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4089}, {\"ngram\": \"incomes\", \"from\": 4095, \"to\": 4102}, {\"ngram\": \"no or low swimming experience\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Access to safe public pools - both as a public health necessity and source of joy in communities - should be the gold standard everywhere.\\\"\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Access\", \"from\": 4155, \"to\": 4161}, {\"ngram\": \"safe public pools\", \"from\": 4165, \"to\": 4182}, {\"ngram\": \"a public health necessity\", \"from\": 4193, \"to\": 4218}, {\"ngram\": \"source\", \"from\": 4223, \"to\": 4229}, {\"ngram\": \"joy\", \"from\": 4233, \"to\": 4236}, {\"ngram\": \"communities\", \"from\": 4240, \"to\": 4251}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold standard\", \"from\": 4264, \"to\": 4281}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These disparities are far from a coincidence; this is by design.\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4362, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These disparities\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4315}, {\"ngram\": \"a coincidence\", \"from\": 4329, \"to\": 4342}, {\"ngram\": \"design\", \"from\": 4355, \"to\": 4361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to limiting pool access, discrimination and disinvestment in majority-Black neighborhoods has led to food deserts and a lack of green spaces, community services and public gathering places - a gutting of what helps communities thrive.\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4609, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 4366, \"to\": 4374}, {\"ngram\": \"pool access\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4398}, {\"ngram\": \"discrimination\", \"from\": 4400, \"to\": 4414}, {\"ngram\": \"disinvestment\", \"from\": 4419, \"to\": 4432}, {\"ngram\": \"majority-Black neighborhoods\", \"from\": 4436, \"to\": 4464}, {\"ngram\": \"food deserts\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4488}, {\"ngram\": \"a lack\", \"from\": 4493, \"to\": 4499}, {\"ngram\": \"green spaces\", \"from\": 4503, \"to\": 4515}, {\"ngram\": \"community services\", \"from\": 4517, \"to\": 4535}, {\"ngram\": \"public gathering places\", \"from\": 4540, \"to\": 4563}, {\"ngram\": \"a gutting\", \"from\": 4566, \"to\": 4575}, {\"ngram\": \"communities\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For many people, what used to be considered \\\"third places\\\" - venues where individuals could spend time relaxing outside of the home and workplace - have become exclusive outposts easily accessible and adequately funded only in wealthier, White neighborhoods.\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4849, \"end\": 4854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\", \"score\": 0.999993686494157, \"rank\": 6.313545831865346e-06, \"text\": \"White\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 4615, \"to\": 4626}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"third places\", \"from\": 4655, \"to\": 4668}, {\"ngram\": \"- venues\", \"from\": 4670, \"to\": 4678}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 4685, \"to\": 4696}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 4709, \"to\": 4713}, {\"ngram\": \"the home\", \"from\": 4734, \"to\": 4742}, {\"ngram\": \"workplace\", \"from\": 4747, \"to\": 4756}, {\"ngram\": \"exclusive outposts\", \"from\": 4771, \"to\": 4789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Third places are incredibly important for public health and wellbeing however because they give people a place to socialize and build community.\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 5014, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Third places\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4882}, {\"ngram\": \"public health\", \"from\": 4912, \"to\": 4925}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4966, \"to\": 4972}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 4973, \"to\": 4980}, {\"ngram\": \"community\", \"from\": 5004, \"to\": 5013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related articleOpinion: The summer skill every kid in America should have Our communities deserve better.\", \"from\": 5016, \"to\": 5122, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Related articleOpinion\", \"from\": 5016, \"to\": 5038}, {\"ngram\": \"The summer skill\", \"from\": 5040, \"to\": 5056}, {\"ngram\": \"every kid\", \"from\": 5057, \"to\": 5066}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 5070, \"to\": 5077}, {\"ngram\": \"Our communities\", \"from\": 5090, \"to\": 5105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lawmakers and community leaders should act on the CDC's recent recommendation to build and revitalize public pools to increase access to swimming for all people.\", \"from\": 5123, \"to\": 5284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5173, \"end\": 5176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1525423204241664e-23, \"text\": \"CDC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q242